Can’t let the season pass without my favorite rosemary pomegranate cocktail/mocktail… and these @lenox collections are making me very excited to ring in the new year. Something about this brand feels like I just hit the jackpot at an antique shop… timeless, classic, and beautiful. SHELBY20 will work until 1.4 for 20% off! Sharing a closer look in my stories and leaving you with the cocktail recipe below! #LovemyLenox #LenoxPartner
-
ROSEMARY POMEGRANATE COCKTAIL/MOCKTAIL:

Servings: 4
Ingredients:
Vodka - 4 oz. (or water, if mocktail)
100% Pomegranate Juice - 2 oz.
Lime - 2 whole limes juiced
Rosemary infused simple sugar - 4 oz. (with 1 rosemary stem)
Blackberries 

To create the simple syrup, boil equal parts water and sugar with a sprig of rosemary. For slightly less sweeter, do 2:1 ratio of water/sugar.

Mix all ingredients in a shaker, pour over ice, and enjoy!
-

Getting in the Valentine’s mood in this cozy @trueandco set 💓& whipped up an appetizer that would also make the perfect addition to a Galentine’s spread. Outfit details are linked in my bio and recipe is below:

Ingredients
- 10-12 large Strawberries, chopped
- 1 Baguette, cut in slices
- 16 oz of Ricotta cheese 
- Basil, chopped
- Balsamic glaze
- Pinch of salt and pepper

Prepare your ingredients - chop strawberries, cut baguette into half inch slices, chop basil, and mix ricotta cheese with salt and pepper. 

Drizzle olive oil on baguette slices and toast for 5-10 minutes or until golden brown. Once baguette is done cooking begin to assemble crostini. Spread 1-2 tbsp of ricotta cheese mixture, add chopped strawberries, and drizzle with balsamic glaze. Finish off with basil and enjoy!

A simple spring lemon pasta salad that makes the perfect side all season long! My secret ingredient for the dressing is @mailleUS Dijon Original, one of the oldest French brands… their mustard has a distinct flavor and texture and is my absolute favorite for homemade dressings! 
INGREDIENTS for dressing:
¼ cup olive oil
¼ cup lemon juice (1 lemon)
2 tbsp Maille Dijon Original 
1 tsp honey
1 clove of garlic

You’ll also need:
Pasta, peas, feta, arugula, thyme, salt and pepper.

Mix all of the ingredients together and enjoy!

A mini brie pumpkin patch for your next charcuterie board addition or fall hosting needs all because I saw one single leaf fall today… I love the mini brie at Trader Joe’s (I’ve spotted some in @citarellagourmetmarket) though and made these last year… SO GOOD.

What You’ll Need:
Puff Pastry
Brie (personal sized)
Blackberries
Pumpkin Butter
Egg
Rosemary
Cinnamon Sticks
Thyme

How To Make:
Cut puff pastry into 5-6 inch squares, add a little pumpkin butter, a few blackberries on top of the brie, and wrap it all up. You’ll wrap it with bakers twine in 8 sections, brush on egg wash, add it to the oven at 375 for 20-25 mins. You can spruce them up with Rosemary, thyme, cinnamon sticks for more of a pumpkiny feel and enjoy!
